matewan ( / ˈmeɪtwɒn / ) is a 1987 american drama film written and directed by john sayles , and starring chris cooper ( in his film debut ) , james earl jones , mary mcdonnell and will oldham , with david strathairn , kevin tighe and gordon clapp in supporting roles .   the film dramatizes the events of the battle of matewan , a coal miners ' strike in 1920 in matewan , a small town in the hills of west virginia .   the film was nominated for the academy award for best cinematography .